    "p-19": {
      "@type": "slate",
      "plaintext": "The sidebar's children list (visible when a container block is selected) has a drag handle (`⋮⋮`) on each child row. Drag it up or down to reorder children **within** the same container. Useful when the children are paged (slides of a slider, panels of an accordion) and you can't drag in the preview because only one is visible at a time. See [Selecting blocks › The children list](selecting-blocks.md#the-children-list-going-down).",
      "value": [
        {
          "type": "p",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "The sidebar's children list (visible when a container block is selected) has a drag handle ("
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "⋮⋮"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": ") on each child row. Drag it up or down to reorder children "
            },
            {
              "type": "strong",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "within"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": " the same container. Useful when the children are paged (slides of a slider, panels of an accordion) and you can't drag in the preview because only one is visible at a time. See "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "data": {
                "url": "selecting-blocks.md#the-children-list-going-down"
              },
              "children": [
